SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 307
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to call a joint convention of the Senate and
House of Representatives for the purpose of
voting on the confirmation of Judge Valerie
Smith to the Tennessee Court of Appeals,
Western Section, and Judge Steven Sword to
the Tennessee Court of Appeals, Eastern
Section, pursuant to Article VI, Section 3 of the
Constitution of Tennessee and Tennessee Code
Annotated, Title 17, Chapter 4.
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that the House of Representatives and the Senate meet
in joint convention on Monday, March 24, 2025, at 3:30 p.m. (CDT) in the chamber of the House
of Representatives to vote on the confirmation of Judge Valerie Smith to the Tennessee Court
of Appeals, Western Section, and to vote on the confirmation of Judge Steven Sword to the
Tennessee Court of Appeals, Eastern Section, pursuant to Article VI, Section 3 of the
Constitution of Tennessee and Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 17, Chapter 4.
